This paper proposes a new network pruning technique for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on the index representation scheme used in pruning and proposes a new compression method using low-rank binary indexing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves computations and matrix operations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
